## 8. Responsive Design

### 8.1 Breakpoint Usage
- Mobile-first approach
- `sm:` (640px) - Small tablets
- `md:` (768px) - Tablets  
- `lg:` (1024px) - Desktop
- Use `md:px-8` instead of `sm:px-6 lg:px-8`

### 8.2 Grid Responsiveness
```jsx
// Cards
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

// Stats
<div className="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
```

## 9. Accessibility Considerations

### 9.1 Color Contrast
- All text combinations must meet WCAG 2.1 AA standards
- Use semantic tokens which are pre-validated for contrast

### 9.2 Focus States
```jsx
className="focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary focus:ring-offset-2"
```

### 9.3 Icon Accessibility
```jsx
<Icon className="h-4 w-4" aria-label="Descriptive text" />
```

## 10. Common Transformations Checklist

When updating a component, follow this checklist:

- [ ] Replace all hardcoded colors with semantic tokens
- [ ] Update spacing to follow 12px grid system
- [ ] Add `bg-background` to page containers
- [ ] Use `shadow-sm` instead of complex shadows
- [ ] Update `rounded-md` to `rounded-xl`
- [ ] Add proper transitions: `duration-150`
- [ ] Enhance typography hierarchy
- [ ] Improve icon sizing and colors
- [ ] Add hover states to interactive elements
- [ ] Use proper card structure with `CardHeader` and `CardContent`
- [ ] Ensure responsive spacing (`px-6 md:px-8`)
- [ ] Test color contrast and accessibility

